description: The V.I.L.E. henchmen botched their assigned crimes, so it's time to send 'em back to school--at Carmen Sandiego's own personal academy of villainy! Unfortunately, their homework results in one of V.I.L.E.'s oddest thefts yet. Does Evan Sawyer, Acme Detective Agency's newest and youngest gumshoe, have what it takes to solve a crime spree as zany as this?
name: The No-Class Classroom

volume.name: Where in the World Is Carmen Sandiego?

description: Carmen Sandiego and her gang are on the loose again...and this time, Carmen seems to be stealing time itself! In a desperate attempt to unravel this latest V.I.L.E. scheme, young hotshot detective Evan Sawyer and new recruit Misty Larkin globetrot the world, with stops in Mexico, England, Tibet, and the world's toughest yogurt bar!
name: Room with a Dj Vu

volume.name: Where in the World Is Carmen Sandiego?

description: Carmen Sandiego has turned her thieving eyes on the treasures of the galaxy! The alien chief of GROK, an Acme Detective Agency satellite organization, summons Evan Sawyer into outer space for help! Can Evan recover the rings of Saturn before Carmen uses them in her newest campaign of villainy?
name: Stealer by Starlight

volume.name: Where in the World Is Carmen Sandiego?

description: 'Kyla Nicolle: Canada's Next Great Super Model?' Its the question everyone is asking in The Great White North. Watch the feisty redhead in head-to-head action against Zootanapuss as 'Zootanapuss vs. High Fashion Models' nears its climax. 'When Sudden Death Isn't Enough For a Girl and Her Bonny: SHOOT-OUT!' In the History of Photorealism section, a close examination of Stan Drake's version of the car crash that claimed the life of Alex Raymond as documented in Arlen Schumer's 'Alex Raymond's Last Ride'.
